		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Dwedit wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I love how MMC1 games are organized so inefficiently than hackers can add support for more characters just by using a different mapper.</div><br />Are you referring to the 4K CHR ROM pages used in SLROM (MMC1 + CHR ROM) games like <a href="http://bootgod.dyndns.org:7777/profile.php?id=7" class="postlink">Chip 'n Dale</a> and <a href="http://bootgod.dyndns.org:7777/profile.php?id=37" class="postlink">Chip 'n Dale 2</a>? I wonder how hard it'd be to make SGROM (MMC1 + CHR RAM) hacks for a lot of these SLROM games to make the characters as configurable as the character in Cocoron.<br /><br />On that note, I seem to remember a <a href="http://www.i-mockery.com/romhacks/donner-party/" class="postlink">total conversion</a> of <a href="http://bootgod.dyndns.org:7777/profile.php?id=211" class="postlink">Monster Party</a> that took advantage of the fact that the player character's frames are repeated in each stage's sprite bank in order to give each part of the story a different player character.

		

